# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Blog submission portal — environment template
#
# Copy this to `.env` and fill in real values for LOCAL development of the
# /submit and /reviewer pages. `.env` is gitignored — never commit real secrets.
#
# In PRODUCTION these are NOT read from a file: they come from GitHub Actions
# secrets/variables → deploy.yml → jac.toml [plugins.scale.secrets] → pod env.
# See .github/SUBMIT_FLOW.md for the full setup.
#
# All three are REQUIRED for sign-in / submit / editor to work. If any are
# missing, those pages degrade to "not configured" (the rest of the blog is
# unaffected). There is NO GitHub App — every GitHub action runs as the
# signed-in user via their OAuth token.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Classic OAuth App (GitHub ▸ Settings ▸ Developer settings ▸ OAuth Apps).
# Callback URL must match where the app is served:
#   prod  → https://blogs.jaseci.org/submit
#   local → http://localhost:8001/submit   (register a second OAuth App for this)
# The app requests the `public_repo` scope so it can fork + open the PR as the user.
GH_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GH_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Signs the session JWT AND derives the key that encrypts the user's GitHub
# token at rest in the session. Generate with:  openssl rand -hex 32
SUBMIT_SESSION_SECRET=

# ── Optional (sensible defaults baked into main.jac) ─────────────────────────
# Target repository and base branch for submission PRs.
# GH_REPO=jaseci-labs/jaseci-blogs
# GH_BASE_BRANCH=main

# Public site origin, used to build "Read live" links for published posts.
# PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://blogs.jaseci.org
